ent dauch served in varied capacities during a year tenure with american axle and manufacturing inc aam a  billion leading global automotive supplier of driveline drivetrain and chassis systems and related components based in detroit mich he most recently served in a global leadership capacity as aam’s executive vice president of worldwide manufacturing and was responsible for the daily operations of  worldwide manufacturing locations including startup plants in poland and china and nearly  employees dauch also held functional leadership roles including president of the metal formed products division director of strategic planning vice president of sales and marketing and vice president of investor relations and financial planning prior to aam dauch worked at the united technologies carrier division where he led the specialty packaged products business consisting of unique product lines produced in korea italy mexico brazil and in several plants across the usa prior to that assignment he was both the materials and manufacturing manager of the small packaged products business unit in tyler texas dauch’s corporate career was preceded by his service as an officer in the us army beginning in  concluding with his assignment as a light infantry company commander with the th mountain division at fort drum ny dauch was also qualified as an airborneranger and expert infantryman dauch is a member of the board of directors of spartan motors inc koch enterprises inc and the heavy duty manufacturers association hdma  in addition he serves as a member of the hmda’s heavy duty business forum  he also serves on the board of directors and is a past president of the army football club dauch earned dual master of science degrees in management and engineering from the massachusetts institute of technology mit and is a graduate of the mit “leaders for manufacturing” program  he earned a bachelor of science degree in engineering from the united states military academy at west point where he was a fouryear football letterman and rhodes scholar candidate email sign up email address customer service call   customerserviceaccuridecorpcom accuride corporation  office circle  evansville indiana      webmasteraccuridecorpcomprivacy and terms of use  site mapaccuride corporate  accuride wheel end solutions  gianetti srl accuride corporation all rights reserved site by gray loon leadership leadership accuride corporate accuride wheel end solutions gianetti route product search accuride’s steel armor for steel wheels accuride’s new quantum ™ aluminum alloy slack adjusters accuflange™ aluminum wheels steel armor roi calculator genuine gunite brake drums accuride acquires majority stake in gianetti ruote srl about business focus business focus – divisions leadership corporate governance bylaws whistleblower policy facilities  locations sales organization code of conduct code of conduct archive history quality “lean management ” guide to lean implementation ehs suppliers supplier code of conduct conflict minerals policy statement conflict minerals disclosure standards  processes payments supplier diversity program logistics  freight routing prospective suppliers supplier forms news careers wages  benefits equal opportunity employer recruiting agencies policy resources contact us navigation menu leadership about menu business focus business focus – divisions leadership corporate governance bylaws whistleblower policy facilities  locations sales organization code of conduct code of conduct archive history quality awards  recognition “lean management ” guide to lean implementation ehs achieving our vision the accuride leadership team has the talent experience and focus to continue to maximize the company’s current success while achieving our vision of becoming the premier supplier of wheelend system solutions to the global commercial vehicle industry executive leadership team richard f dauch president  ceo accuride corporation bio » mary e blair senior vice presid