facturing inc since october   and served as its president of metal formed products division since january  mr dauch served as the president of metal formed products division at american axle  manufacturing holdings inc since january  and also served as its vice president of metal formed products division since june  vice president of investor relations since september  vice president of financial planning from september  to september  vice president of sales and marketing since january  vice president of sales since january  vice president of manufacturing of driveline division since july  vice president of manufacturing since august  director of strategic and capacity planning since february  and plant manager of detroit gear  axle plant since may  mr dauch joined american axle  manufacturing holdings inc in may  as served as a corporate manager of labor relations until may  prior to american axle  manufacturing holdings inc he served as a senior business manager and business unit manager at united technologies corporation from july  prior to his automotive career he served in the us army for eleven years at assignments including platoon leader and company commander he began a military career in  as an officer in the us army an airborne ranger his military assignments included combat engineer platoon leader executive officer battalion adjutant and light infantry company commander in the th mountain division he also served as the cochairman of the board of directors of technology startup microheat inc he has been a director of accuride corp since february   he has been an independent director of spartan motors inc since february  he serves as a director of koch enterprises inc he serves as a director of transportation technologies industries inc the original equipment suppliers association oesa division of the motor  equipment manufacturers association mema michigan manufacturers association and st joseph mercy oakland foundation he has been a director of heavy duty manufacturers association since january   he has been a member of the hdma heavy duty business forum of industry leaders since  he also is a member of the board of directors and served as president of the us army football club and is a member of the evansville regional business committee he also served as a member of the board of directors of the society of manufacturing engineers sme education foundation mr dauch earned dual master of science degrees in management and engineering from the massachusetts institute of technology mit and a bachelor of science degree in engineering and economic management from the united states military academy at west pointread full background corporate headquarters  office circleevansville indiana united statesphone fax  board members memberships directorkoch enterprises incpresentindependent directorspartan motors incpresentchief executive officer president and directoraccuride corporationpresentdirectorheavy duty manufacturers association education ms massachusetts institute of technologybs united states military academy other affiliations american axle  manufacturing holdings incspartan motors inctransportation technologies industries incacument global technologies incmassachusetts institute of technologykoch enterprises incunited states military academyaccuride wheel end solutionsamerican axle  manufacturing incheavy duty manufacturers association annual compensation salarybonustotal annual compensation stocks options restricted stock awardsall other compensationexercisable optionstotal number of options total compensation total annual cash compensationtotal short term compensationother long term compensationtotal calculated compensation request profile update   the information and data displayed in this profile are created and managed by sp global market intelligence a division of sp global bloombergcom does not create or control the content for inquiries please contact sp global market intelligence directly by clicking here sto