y to be the true “moments of his life”born in norwalk ohio on july   to wg albert and helen dauch who preceded him in death survived by his siblings gale dee nancy william mona jack lee david carol and his foster brother george knittle mary lou also his late brotherinlaw bartondauch graduated from ashland high school in ashland ohio in  he earned allohio honors in football and became a proud purdue boilermaker when he received a scholarship to play football earning several varsity letters he received his bachelor of science degree in industrial management in  upon his college graduation he started his career in the auto industry joining general motors at their chevrolet flint assembly plant where he went through management training and various plant supervisory positions in  he became the plant manager at the chevrolet spring  bumper plant in livonia making him at age  the youngest plant manager in gm’s history at that time his next assignment was in the detroit zone sales operations for a year his final assignment for gm was as plant manager of the detroit gear  axle manufacturing complexhe left gm in  to join volkswagen of america to become their vicepresident and general manufacturing manager later being promoted to group vicepresident and board of directors member in recognition of his immense influence on vw’s successful launching of volkswagen production in americain  he joined chrysler corporation where he was able to lead manufacturing initiatives to improve quality production and labor his key innovations were three shift assembly just in time materials management and sequential production “dick was practicing lean manufacturing and leading the quality revolution years before those terms became part of the business conversation” said former chrysler chairman lee iacocca “he put his heart and soul into the auto industry and the success of aam is proof of this dedication”dauch was the cofounder of american axle  manufacturing aam in march  he served as chairman of the board from  until his passing most recently he served as executive chairman of the board he also served as chief executive officer from  to  and was president of aam from march  to december  he was known for his distinctive direct getitdone style of management that helped aam become one of the top automotive suppliers in the world and traded on the new york stock exchange under the symbol axlformer michigan governor john engler worked closely with him through the years he remembers “dick’s vision became reality failing plants became profitable a blighted area of urban detroit became an oasis and aam produced products that succeeded globally dick dauch showed us how that vision can be replicated nationally and internationally applying the lesson of detroit and axle leadership and team building quality and innovation to us manufacturing and our nation’s economy”he was the recipient of numerous honors during his career he received the  shienming wu foundation manufacturing leadership award the  ceo legend award from automation alley the  harvard business school of michigan business statesman the  wayne state university college of business administrations michigan executive of the year and the detroit regional chamber’s world leader of the year dauch was also named detroit news michiganian of the year  crains detroit business newsmaker of the year  michigan manufacturers association “manufacturer of the year”  and the automotive hall of fame industry leader of the year  and he received the ellis island medal of honor dauch’s reputation as an innovative manufacturing strategist and entrepreneur is widely recognized in north america and around the world in addition to lecturing extensively on the subject of worldclass manufacturing he authored two books passion for manufacturing and american drive which was released in dauch sat on the board of directors of the national association of manufacturers nam and served as chairman of the manufacturing institute he is a past member of the board of directors of detroit renaissance and the board of the detroit economic club in  dauch served as the general chair of the united way for southeast michigan’s torch drive campaign he was past chairman of the board of directors of the detroit regional chamber he was very involved in the boys and girls clubs of southeastern michigan and the boy scouts of americadetroit area council which presented him with its “man and boy award” in  in  dauch was honored with the distinguished citizen award and was also presented with six merit badges reflecting his involvement in athletics his citizenship and his career in the automotive industrya big supporter of education he was instrumental in creating manufacturing and management curricula at several universities including purdue university lehigh university and the massachusetts institute of technology he received an honorary doctorate of management from purdue university an honorary doctorate of law from ashland university ohio and an honorary doctor of commercial science from central michigan universitygenerous donations from the dauch family helped create the richard e and sandra j dauch college of business and economics at ashland university the dauch center for management of manufacturing enterprises at purdue university and the dick and sandy dauch alumni center also at purdue in addition the dauchs partnered with the nfl to establish the nflyet boys  girls club at the dick  sandy dauch campus in detroit michigan they also collaborated with the boy scouts of america to establish the dauch scout center in detroitunafraid of controversy or hardship throughout his career dauch did whatever it took to get the job done in his book american drive dauch declared “i hope to live long enough to see one or more us auto companies listed again among the dow jones  but even if i don’t i do believe us manufacturing will continue to grow and prosper and lead our country back to a solid economic footing it is already happening we have only begun to show what we can do manufacturers in the usa have accepted the challenge of world competition and are poised for great things in the years ahead i am fiercely proud of the creation success and sustainability of aam based in detroit michigan we are one of america’s premier global automotive manufacturers we have done it against all odds it has been greatly fulfilling”family will receive friends monday august  and tuesday august  pmpm at aj desmond  sons vasu rodgers  connell chapel  woodward between  mile royal oak funeral service will be held on wednesday august  am at first united methodist church  w maple rd birmingham mi with a visitation preceding the service beginning at am in lieu of flowers the family suggests memorial tributes to “richard e dauch memorial fund” to support research and education in the fight against pancreatic cancer beaumont foundation po box  troy mi  or hospice of michigan  mack avenue detroit mi  for more information american axle  manufacturing url  wwwaamcom advertisement place your ad here recent articles measuring left and right july  ask not what your heat treater can do for you july  micropulse and microshift for ground bevel gearsets july  find more articles on recent news walter ag digital solutions to be on display at emo  july   third wave systems advantedge software expanded to include gear machining july   sandvik coromant introduces coroplus suite of solutions for mastercam  july   affolter af universal loading system offers three methods for part feeding july   heule tool cofac series carbide coated blades designed for deburring elliptical and contoured surfaces july